# Frontend Agent Instructions

## Tech Stack
- **Vue 3** with `<script setup lang="ts">` (Composition API)
- **TypeScript** — strict mode, no `any`
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — utility-first CSS via `@tailwindcss/vite`
- **shadcn-vue** — headless UI components built on `radix-vue`
- **VueUse** — composable utilities (`@vueuse/core`)
- **Pinia** — state management
- **Axios** — HTTP client (via `src/services/api.ts`)
- **Prettier** — code formatting
- **ESLint** — linting (TypeScript + Vue rules)

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/
│   └── ui/            # shadcn-vue components (Button, Card, etc.)
├── composables/       # VueUse-style composables (useItems.ts, etc.)
├── lib/
│   └── utils.ts       # cn() helper for Tailwind class merging
├── services/
│   └── api.ts         # Axios API client + typed endpoint functions
├── stores/            # Pinia stores (global state)
├── views/             # Page-level components
├── router/            # Vue Router configuration
└── style.css          # Tailwind CSS + shadcn CSS variables
```

## Conventions

### Components
- All components use `<script setup lang="ts">`
- Use `defineProps<{}>()` with TypeScript interfaces (not runtime validators)
- UI primitives go in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn-vue pattern)
- Feature components go in `src/components/`

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref } from 'vue'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

const count = ref(0)
</script>

<template>
  <Button @click="count++">Count: {{ count }}</Button>
</template>
```

### Composables
- Prefix with `use` (e.g., `useItems`, `useAuth`)
- Use `@vueuse/core` utilities where possible (`useAsyncState`, `useFetch`, `useStorage`, etc.)
- Return `readonly()` refs for data to prevent external mutation

```ts
import { ref, readonly } from 'vue'
import { useAsyncState } from '@vueuse/core'

export function useMyFeature() {
  const data = ref<MyType[]>([])
  const { isLoading, error } = useAsyncState(async () => {
    data.value = await myApi.list()
  }, undefined)
  return { data: readonly(data), isLoading, error }
}
```

### API Services
- All API calls go through `src/services/api.ts`
- Define TypeScript interfaces for all request/response types
- Group related endpoints into named objects (e.g., `itemsApi`)

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` to conditionally merge classes
- Use shadcn-vue CSS variables (`--background`, `--primary`, etc.) for theming
- Never write custom CSS unless Tailwind cannot achieve the result

### Adding a New shadcn-vue Component
```bash
# Manual approach: create in src/components/ui/<component>/
# Follow the pattern of existing components (Button, Card)
```

## Commands
```bash
pnpm dev              # Start dev server
pnpm build            # Type-check + build
pnpm type-check       # Run vue-tsc --noEmit
pnpm lint             # ESLint with auto-fix
pnpm lint:check       # ESLint check only
pnpm format           # Prettier write
pnpm format:check     # Prettier check
```
